      <body>Specifically, docs for url_for claim :only_path defaults to false.  However, setting :host without explicitly specifying :only_path =&gt; false results in a relative url.

That is:

    url_for foo, :host =&gt; &quot;bla.com&quot;

... provides a relative path but ...

    url_for foo, :host =&gt; &quot;bla.com&quot;, :only_path =&gt; false

... provides an absolute path.</body>
      <body-html>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Specifically, docs for url_for claim :only_path defaults to
false. However, setting :host without explicitly specifying
:only_path =&amp;gt; false results in a relative url.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;That is:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;
&lt;code&gt;url_for foo, :host =&amp;gt; &quot;bla.com&quot;&lt;/code&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;... provides a relative path but ...&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;
&lt;code&gt;url_for foo, :host =&amp;gt; &quot;bla.com&quot;, :only_path =&amp;gt; false&lt;/code&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;... provides an absolute path.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</body-html>
